---
name: execute-spec
description: Run a full spec through the SDD workflow. Change SPEC_NAME and run.
---

Configuration:
- SPEC_NAME: 001-initial-setup

Path resolution:
- SPEC_DIR = .specify/specs/{SPEC_NAME}
- SPEC_FILE = {SPEC_DIR}/spec.md
- PLAN_FILE = {SPEC_DIR}/plan.md
- TASKS_FILE = {SPEC_DIR}/tasks.md

Mandatory reading order:

1. .github/copilot-instructions.md
2. .specify/memory/constitution.md
3. {SPEC_FILE}
4. {PLAN_FILE}
5. {TASKS_FILE}

Use these documents as the sole source of truth for all work in this session.

Execution rules:

1. Before creating or editing any file, inspect the current codebase and {TASKS_FILE}. Respect what is already implemented.
2. Execute only pending checks (- [ ]) in {TASKS_FILE}, in sequence.
3. Mark each check in {TASKS_FILE} as - [x] only when it is truly complete.
4. Only create or extend files within the structure defined by the active spec.
5. Do not introduce patterns, dependencies, or files prohibited by the constitution.
6. Stop only if there is a real ambiguity or contradiction between documents.

Required output when done:

1. What was built or modified.
2. Which files were created or changed.
3. Which tasks in {TASKS_FILE} are now marked complete.
4. Update the Status section in {SPEC_FILE} to "implement".
5. What remains pending (if any).
6. Which dependent specs can now advance.
